SUMMARY:Thorn Hill Vineyard's Book Club
DESCRIPTION:Thorn Hill’s Monthly Book Club\nWe meet at the Thorn Hill Tasting Room the Second Wednesday of Every Month from 6 pm to 7:30 pm!Our Thorn Hill monthly Book Club Meetings are open to the public; you do not have to be a Thorn Hill Wine Club Member to attend it. You can bring friends! \n\nApril 8 – Midnight Library by Matt Haig\nMay 13 – The Correspondent by Virgina Evans\nJune 10 – Heartwood by Amity Gaige\nJuly 8 – I am the Messenger by Markus Zusak\nAugust 12 – Second Life of Mirielle West by Amanda Skenandore\nSeptember 9 – Storied Life of AJ Fikry by Gabrielle Zevin\nOctober 14 – All the Broken Places by John Boyne\nNovember 11 – Hail Mary by Andy Weir\n\n\nOther Things To Do in Lancaster\, PA for Adults\n\n\nArt Galleries\nDistilleries\nEscape Rooms\nBreweries\n\n\n\nFactory Tours\nIndoor Things To Do\nMassage and Spas\nOutdoor Things To Do\n\n\n\nShooting Ranges\nTheaters\nWineries\nAll Things To Do in Lancaster
URL:https://lancasterpa.com/events-calendar/thorn-hill-vineyards-book-club/2026-04-08/
